		  Installation Instructions for Griz4s

			  ** Version 12.1 **

			Updated March 22, 2013


******************************************************************************************
Griz requires Mili version 11.1 or later. The following gnu tools are also
requited:  gmake

Once the Griz tarfile has been extracted, execute the following steps in this order:


(1) cd to the directory GrizDist
    change the date in file misc.h to todays date

(2) Enter the command: ./configure --enable-png --with-mili= ** directory 
								path for mili you built **

(3) A new directory will be created - it with start with "GRIZ4", 
    for example: GRIZ4-chaos_3_x86_64-YANA/

    cd to this directory

(4) Enter the command: gmake clobber; gmake opt

(5) The Griz execution script called "griz4s" can be found in the directory
    /bin_opt

(6) To run Griz, enter the command:  griz4s -i input_file


** Livermore Specific **

(7) To install an executable on the LC machines do the following:
    a). Perform steps 1-5 above
    b). give mdgadmin griz4s.linux_opt
    c). xsu mdgadmin
    d). cd /usr/apps/mdg/archive/grizdir/[grizalpha|grizbeta|grizversion]/bin
    e). mv griz4s.linux_opt griz4s.linux_opt-MMMDDYYYY
    f). take username
    g). chmod 750 griz4s.linux_opt_batch
    h). chgrp mdgusers griz4s.linux_opt
    i). Most Important - logout as mdgadmin and run a test using the new installed version

(8) To build and install the batch version of Griz:
    a). Perform steps 1-4 above
          New Step 5 - > gmake clobber; gmake batch_opt
    b). give mdgadmin griz4s.linux_opt_batch
    c). xsu mdgadmin
    d). cd /usr/apps/mdg/archive/grizdir/[grizalpha|grizbeta|grizversion]/bin
    e). mv griz4s.linux_opt griz4s.linux_opt_batch-MMMDDYYYY
    f). take username
    g). chmod 750 griz4s.linux_opt_batch
    h). chgrp mdgusers griz4s.linux_opt_batch
    i). Most Important - logout as mdgadmin and run a test using the new installed batch version
